During a meeting in the aftermath of a tornado in Kentucky, President Biden expressed his amazement at the way people came together to help each other. He emphasized the importance of unity and support during times of disaster and assured the community that federal assistance would be available not just immediately, but also in the months to come. Governor Beshear provided an update on the state's response efforts, including deploying National Guard and other workers, opening state parks for shelter, and restoring cell service and power. Secretary Mayorkas highlighted the government's commitment to providing necessary resources and assistance, including disaster recovery centers and a dedicated website and phone line for survivors. FEMA Administrator Criswell praised the local and state leaders, first responders, and community members for their heroic efforts and emphasized the whole-of-community approach to recovery. She also mentioned the availability of individual assistance for impacted individuals.